ipxact:register.ipxact:name: RST_CNTRS
ipxact:register.ipxact:description: Reset read/write hit/miss counters by writing any value to this register.

ipxact:register.ipxact:name: INVALIDATE
ipxact:register.ipxact:description: Invalidate the cache data contents by writing any value to this register.

ipxact:register.ipxact:name: version
ipxact:register.ipxact:description: Product version. This 16-bit register uses nibbles to represent decimal numbers using their binary values. The two most significant nibbles represent the integral part of the version, and the two least significant nibbles represent the decimal part. For example V12.34 is represented by 0x1234.

ipxact:port.ipxact:name: invalidate_i
ipxact:port.ipxact:description: Invalidates all cache lines instantaneously if high.

ipxact:port.ipxact:name: invalidate_o
ipxact:port.ipxact:description: This output is asserted high when the cache is invalidated via the cache controller or the direct {\tt invalidate_in} signal. The present {\tt invalidate_out} signal is useful for invalidating the next-level cache if there is one. If not, this output should be floated.

ipxact:port.ipxact:name: wtb_empty_i
ipxact:port.ipxact:description: This input is driven by the next-level cache, if there is one, when its write-through buffer is empty. It should be tied high if there is no next-level cache. This signal is used to compute the overall empty status of a cache hierarchy, as explained for signal {\tt wtb_empty_out}.

ipxact:port.ipxact:name: wtb_empty_o
ipxact:port.ipxact:description: This output is high if the cache's write-through buffer is empty and its { t wtb_empty_in} signal is high. This signal informs that all data written to the cache has been written to the destination memory module, and all caches on the way are empty.

ipxact:parameter.ipxact:name: LRU
ipxact:parameter.ipxact:description: Least Recently Used -- more resources intensive - N*log2(N) bits per cache line - Uses counters

ipxact:parameter.ipxact:name: PLRU_MRU
ipxact:parameter.ipxact:description: bit-based Pseudo-Least-Recently-Used, a simpler replacement policy than LRU, using a much lower complexity (lower resources) - N bits per cache line

ipxact:parameter.ipxact:name: PLRU_TREE
ipxact:parameter.ipxact:description: tree-based Pseudo-Least-Recently-Used, uses a tree that updates after any way received an hit, and points towards the oposing one. Uses less resources than bit-pseudo-lru - N-1 bits per cache line

ipxact:parameter.ipxact:name: WRITE_THROUGH
ipxact:parameter.ipxact:description: write-through not allocate: implements a write-through buffer

ipxact:parameter.ipxact:name: WRITE_BACK
ipxact:parameter.ipxact:description: write-back allocate: implementes a dirty-memory

ipxact:parameter.ipxact:name: ADDR_W_CSRS
ipxact:parameter.ipxact:description: Address width of CSRs

ipxact:parameter.ipxact:name: FE_ADDR_W
ipxact:parameter.ipxact:description: Front-end address width (log2): defines the total memory space accessible via the cache, which must be a power of two.

ipxact:parameter.ipxact:name: FE_DATA_W
ipxact:parameter.ipxact:description: Front-end data width (log2): this parameter allows supporting processing elements with various data widths.

ipxact:parameter.ipxact:name: BE_ADDR_W
ipxact:parameter.ipxact:description: Back-end address width (log2): the value of this parameter must be equal or greater than FE_ADDR_W to match the width of the back-end interface, but the address space is still dictated by ADDR_W.

ipxact:parameter.ipxact:name: BE_DATA_W
ipxact:parameter.ipxact:description: Back-end data width (log2): the value of this parameter must be an integer multiple $k \geq 1$ of DATA_W. If $k>1$, the memory controller can operate at a frequency higher than the cache's frequency. Typically, the memory controller has an asynchronous FIFO interface, so that it can sequentially process multiple commands received in paralell from the cache's back-end interface.

ipxact:parameter.ipxact:name: NWAYS_W
ipxact:parameter.ipxact:description: Number of cache ways (log2): the miminum is 0 for a directly mapped cache; the default is 1 for a two-way cache; the maximum is limited by the desired maximum operating frequency, which degrades with the number of ways.

ipxact:parameter.ipxact:name: NLINES_W
ipxact:parameter.ipxact:description: Line offset width (log2): the value of this parameter equals the number of cache lines, given by 2**NLINES_W.

ipxact:parameter.ipxact:name: WORD_OFFSET_W
ipxact:parameter.ipxact:description: Word offset width (log2): the value of this parameter equals the number of words per line, which is 2**OFFSET_W.

ipxact:parameter.ipxact:name: WTBUF_DEPTH_W
ipxact:parameter.ipxact:description: Write-through buffer depth (log2). A shallow buffer will fill up more frequently and cause write stalls; however, on a Read After Write (RAW) event, a shallow buffer will empty faster, decreasing the duration of the read stall. A deep buffer is unlkely to get full and cause write stalls; on the other hand, on a RAW event, it will take a long time to empty and cause long read stalls.

ipxact:parameter.ipxact:name: REP_POLICY
ipxact:parameter.ipxact:description: Line replacement policy: set to 0 for Least Recently Used (LRU); set to 1 for Pseudo LRU based on Most Recently Used (PLRU_MRU); set to 2 for tree-based Pseudo LRU (PLRU_TREE).

ipxact:parameter.ipxact:name: WRITE_POL
ipxact:parameter.ipxact:description: Write policy: set to 0 for write-through or set to 1 for write-back.

ipxact:parameter.ipxact:name: USE_CTRL
ipxact:parameter.ipxact:description: Instantiates a cache controller (1) or not (0). The cache controller provides memory-mapped software accessible registers to invalidate the cache data contents, and monitor the write through buffer status using the front-end interface. To access the cache controller, the MSB of the address mut be set to 1. For more information refer to the example software functions provided.

ipxact:parameter.ipxact:name: USE_CTRL_CNT
ipxact:parameter.ipxact:description: Instantiates hit/miss counters for reads, writes or both (1), or not (0). This parameter is meaningful if the cache controller is present (USE_CTRL: 1), providing additional software accessible functions for these functions.

ipxact:parameter.ipxact:name: FE_NBYTES
ipxact:parameter.ipxact:description: Default description

ipxact:parameter.ipxact:name: FE_NBYTES_W
ipxact:parameter.ipxact:description: Default description

ipxact:parameter.ipxact:name: BE_NBYTES
ipxact:parameter.ipxact:description: Default description

ipxact:parameter.ipxact:name: BE_NBYTES_W
ipxact:parameter.ipxact:description: Default description

ipxact:parameter.ipxact:name: LINE2BE_W
ipxact:parameter.ipxact:description: Default description

ipxact:parameter.ipxact:name: ADDR_W
ipxact:parameter.ipxact:description: Width of the (word aligned) front-end address bus, optionally including the highest bit to access cache controller CSRs (if enabled)

ipxact:parameter.ipxact:name: DATA_W
ipxact:parameter.ipxact:description: Default description

ipxact:parameter.ipxact:name: AXI
ipxact:parameter.ipxact:description: AXI interface used by backend

ipxact:parameter.ipxact:name: AXI_ID_W
ipxact:parameter.ipxact:description: AXI ID width

ipxact:parameter.ipxact:name: AXI_ID
ipxact:parameter.ipxact:description: AXI ID

ipxact:parameter.ipxact:name: AXI_LEN_W
ipxact:parameter.ipxact:description: AXI length

ipxact:parameter.ipxact:name: AXI_ADDR_W
ipxact:parameter.ipxact:description: AXI address width

ipxact:parameter.ipxact:name: AXI_DATA_W
ipxact:parameter.ipxact:description: AXI data width

ipxact:parameter.ipxact:name: VERSION
ipxact:parameter.ipxact:description: Product version. This 16-bit macro uses nibbles to represent decimal numbers using their binary values. The two most significant nibbles represent the integral part of the version, and the two least significant nibbles represent the decimal part.
